review_blob: Hipster, does it exist in the sierras? Yes it does. On tap at brewery would be a 5+++++ this Bronson is the quintessential BW... How they mix the hops the grain malt character and do the dirty dancing with the Swaze...I dunno. Hops malt rich rich thick malts without the bitterness from the grains is stupendilicious...

Hipster, does it exist??? Yes it does...so does Bigfoot, but that is different mountain range. Rich big chocolate roast, slight alcohol, licorice nite made this amazeballs!! Another one to not pound or you will be ralphing in the bowl. The favors in this are totally superb!.,!
beer_name: Great Divide Yeti Imperial Stout - Oak Aged

review_blob: Hipster, NASCAR, if I actually have to rate this perfectly clear H2O you are all totes. Grain dust filtered poo poo. If you have to drink this so you dont get hurt at a race event then I will understand.
Hipster, Dads beer. H2O with some grain dust. If you need a headache to avoid sex....suck this down. Youll pee all night and for nothing better than showing you can pound a Bronson.
Hipster wanna be, metallic alcoholic, grain, tangerine peel aroma...meh...remember the iron cross west coast...change label??? Sarah palin pig different face. Go for the stone!!!

Hipster Mercedes Benz. Usually over rated, but still one if the best cars and brews. Oily hoppy lupin madness. Great bubblie great roundabout throughout the whole Bronson. Will kick you in the rear if you pound these. Usually pretty available, but got to know the shops. Dont see it on tap.

Hipster OG, for sure this one is the OG if Bronsons. Unreal killer sour oak cedar cellar mold basement cheese... You cant do this in US as it take 4 ever to jones this one. Bucket list to go there and drink from the brewery!

Hipster, overseas. The champ!! Wheat here like in minimal quant. Almost cherry like alcohol on the back of throat. Champagne beer ...not miller...real champagne. Readily available so at your fav carne casa, it is there. Best with a big piece of red flesh and a creamy sauce.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Hipster hop perfection. I cant do a rumble more than the hops do along the palate. Killer hoppy brew, grass, light oily lupine aroma and flavor. Unreal finish. Off the shelf. Impress anyone bringing thus to the party.
Hipster in a can. Great name and in a enviro can. Great amber with a herbal Cush taste and aroma...pretty sick Bronson to pound. Great bubblie, great finish.

Hipster, so three days ago. This brew is fraking everywhere. I see this on tap more than bud. Dont tobey me it is a great brew wonderful hop aroma grata dry tadte. Slightly metallic great clarity for the joneses, however step up from this gateway Bronson and do a fruit lambic!!!!

Hipster organic. Roast coffee, extremely drinkable. Not off chart but organic. Oh it feels so good to pound a few Bronsons, not get to FUBAR and know you are not ingesting GMO. One if best organically around
beer_name: Santa Cruz Mountain Organic Devout Stout

review_blob: Hipster big boy perfection. Everything from roast, anise, alcohol, warmth, bubblie, is off the hook. Do not, repeat do not slam this bad boy unless you want to worship the pooper. If you get a chance to get this, it is a must.
beer_name: The Bruery Black Tuesday Imperial Stout

review_blob: Hipster lobby beer. Hanging out with the tivs in a hotel lobby. This will always be there. Hipsters from out of the zip code will love gargoyle. But as for beer. Always solid, always consistent, wonderful hoppy aroma, real clear not anal tort will bag on weird looking brew. Great finish.

Hipster, everywhere. Need a farmhouse or saison to be cool. This is it. Grapefruit some sour orange peel, anyone can cruise with this Bronson. Easy to find, best on tap. Higher ABV. Dies not taste like it. Perfect with mellow cheeses. Get at your local grill with cheese platter. Each different cheese can bring out each distinct fruity tart notes.
beer_name: Boulevard Smokestack Series - Tank 7 Farmhouse Ale

review_blob: Hipster latest n greatest. Lemon sour, like lemon drop. In fact I put sugar on rim for my second flute. LPR,LPD or LPM what ever you wanna call it, this will make a chipper out of any Betty. It is real sour, some oak, some cellar, some bubblie, overall amazeballs.
Hipster OC. Totally Awks. Not in a fin way but pretty good. Strange hops, strange roast, and a cedar note. Abundance of flavor but couldnt pound a bunch. Just enjoy the one.
Hipster Nor Cal Especial. Love the oak, love the cellar woodie character, cloudy. Somewhat sour. This one has been on clothesline down south for only a scont. But well worth a try!
beer_name: The Rare Barrel Shadows of Their Eyes

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Hipster, unfound. So hard to come by and loads of kale to get. Not a Brobson to pound. Very tart sour, but opus of brews. Slight salty aftertaste but added to thin carbonation, very trippy and on the deck. Nothing like this tart brew with cellar wine characteristics and woodie notes. Stupendilicious.
Hipster cheapie. Flaccid nothing to it but gets you the buzz. A perfect Bronson when on special and local joint. Only do it with the peeps. Otherwise the snobs will shank you. Again just grain n H2O

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Hipster go to. Has all you need with loads of fruit, and super sweet tart. Always a good brew to have anywhere, cool to cold is best. Goes well with all food. Especially arugula and basal dressing.
